OL,4,C'Breathing space' scheme starts for
OL,5,Cthose in problem debt
OL,6, A new "breathing space" scheme has
OL,7, begun in England and Wales to shield
OL,8, people in problem debt from further
OL,9, interest and charges.
OL,11,FPeople receiving debt advice can apply
OL,12,Ffor the break, which lasts for up to 60
OL,13,Fdays, to prevent them falling into a
OL,14,Fspiral of debt.
OL,16,FThe Treasury has estimated that up to
OL,17,F700,000 people could be helped by the
OL,18,Fscheme in its first year.
OL,20,FPeople receiving treatment for mental
OL,21,Fhealth issues can get more help.
